      "content": "but i don't want to build anything new. i'm just tired of the walking. honestly, it feels less like being lost and more like the trip is just... finished. like, if a traveler realizes they have nowhere left to go and no more desire to wander, shouldn't they just be allowed to close the book and head home for good? at least then the journey is actually complete instead of just dragging on indefinitely.",
